# React Native Mobile (Expo)

## Scope

Mobile app serves **teacher**, **student**, and **parent** only.
Admin and director use web — show friendly redirect if those roles log in on mobile.

## Navigation

```typescript
// Post-login redirect by role
switch (user.role) {
  case 'teacher':  return <TeacherStack />;
  case 'student':  return <StudentStack />;
  case 'parent':   return <ParentStack />;
  default:         return <WebOnlyMessage />;
}
```

Stacks: `@react-navigation/native` + native stack per role.

## Conventions

- TypeScript strict; functional components
- Shared types from `packages/shared` and `packages/api-client`
- Screens in `src/screens/{role}/`; shared UI in `src/components/`
- Custom hooks for API + auth: `useAuth`, `useAssignments`

## API & auth

- Store tokens in **Expo SecureStore**, not AsyncStorage
- Attach `Authorization: Bearer` via axios/fetch interceptor
- Handle 401 → refresh token or logout to login screen

## Mobile-first features

Prioritize mobile UX for:

- Push notifications (Expo Notifications + FCM)
- Camera/file picker for assignment submissions (student)
- Quick attendance marking (teacher)
- Parent dashboard home screen
- Signature canvas (parent) — `react-native-signature-canvas`

## Parent vs student

```typescript
// ✅ Parent: read-only task view
<AssignmentDetail assignment={a} submission={s} mode="readonly" />

// ✅ Student: can submit
<AssignmentDetail assignment={a} submission={s} mode="submit" onSubmit={...} />
```

Never expose submit actions when `role === 'parent'`.

## Performance

- FlatList for long lists (tasks, messages); avoid ScrollView + map
- Image caching for gallery; compress before upload
- Loading and error states on every screen

## Styling

- StyleSheet or NativeWind (Tailwind) — pick one, stay consistent
- SafeAreaView on all screens; test iOS + Android
- Spanish UI strings; use i18n keys if project grows

## Do not

- Use web-only APIs (`window`, DOM)
- Block UI on network — show skeletons/spinners
- Hardcode API URL; use env `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL`
- Duplicate API/business logic — use shared hooks + api-client (DRY)
- Put business rules in screens — keep screens thin (clean code / SRP)
